## 5. Content Pipeline

### Content Lifecycle (`contents`)

```sql
CREATE TABLE `contents` (
  `user_id`      bigint UNSIGNED,
  `brand_id`     char(36),          -- Optional brand association
  `type`         varchar(30),       -- post / caption / ad / email / script / blog
  `title`        varchar(191),
  `body`         longtext,          -- AI-generated content
  `status`       varchar(20),       -- draft / published / archived
  `is_flagged`   tinyint(1),        -- Content moderation flag
  `flag_reason`  varchar(255),      -- Why it was flagged
  `version`      int,               -- Current version number
  `meta`         json,              -- Flexible metadata (tone, platform, prompt used)
  `credits_cost` int                -- How many credits this generation cost
);
```

### Version Control (`content_versions`)

Every content edit creates a version snapshot:

```sql
CREATE TABLE `content_versions` (
  `content_id` char(36),
  `version`    int,          -- Matches contents.version at time of save
  `title`      varchar(191),
  `body`       longtext,
  `meta`       json
);
KEY `content_versions_content_id_version_index` (content_id, version)
```

This is a complete content audit trail — users can revert to any previous AI generation or edit, and the platform can track how content evolves from first draft to final post.

### Content Assets (`content_assets`)

```sql
CREATE TABLE `content_assets` (
  `brand_id`  char(36),
  `type`      varchar(30),       -- image / logo / video / audio
  `disk`      varchar(30),       -- storage driver (public / s3 / etc.)
  `path`      varchar(191),      -- file path
  `mime_type` varchar(80),
  `bytes`     bigint UNSIGNED,
  `meta`      json
);
KEY `content_assets_brand_id_type_index` (brand_id, type)
```

Assets are scoped per brand, not per user — enabling shared brand media libraries across team members on the same brand profile.

