### Three-Gateway Architecture

```json
{
  "payment_provider":        "nowpayments",
  "nowpayments_api_key":     "ghttyyy",
  "nowpayments_ipn_secret":  "hhhhhh",
  "stripe_api_key":          "hhhjjj",
  "stripe_webhook_secret":   "ddddddgf",
  "paystack_public_key":     "hfhfhfh",
  "paystack_secret_key":     "rstrttrsrg"
}
```

The platform supports three simultaneous payment providers:

| Provider | Type | Primary Market | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| **NowPayments** | Crypto | Global | Default provider at launch |
| **Stripe** | Fiat (card) | Global | Standard card billing |
| **Paystack** | Fiat (card) | Africa (NG, GH, KE, ZA) | West African market coverage |

> **Note:** Keys in the dump are placeholder values (`ghttyyy`, `hhhjjj`) — test environment credentials only. Production keys are injected via environment variables.

### Crypto Transactions (`crypto_transactions`)

```sql
CREATE TABLE `crypto_transactions` (
  `user_id`        bigint UNSIGNED,
  `subscription_id` char(36),
  `processor`       varchar(30),       -- 'nowpayments'
  `amount_cents`    int,
  `currency`        varchar(10),       -- 'USD'
  `status`          varchar(20),       -- waiting / confirming / confirmed / failed
  `tx_hash`         varchar(120),      -- On-chain transaction hash
  `invoice_id`      varchar(120),      -- NowPayments invoice ID
  `webhook_payload` json               -- Full IPN webhook payload retained
);
KEY `crypto_transactions_status_created_at_index` (status, created_at)
```

The `(status, created_at)` index targets the most critical operational query — "find all pending crypto transactions older than X minutes" — used by the job processor to detect stale payments.

