## 11. Schema Design Observations

### Strengths

| Pattern | Detail |
|---|---|
| UUID primary keys throughout | All business entity tables use `char(36)` UUIDs — no sequential ID exposure in URLs |
| Soft deletes on key tables | `deleted_at` on `affiliates`, `brand_profiles`, `contents`, `workflows` |
| Dual analytics layers | Raw events + daily rollups with upsert-friendly UNIQUE key |
| Content version history | Full snapshot history on every content edit via `content_versions` |
| `(workflow_id, position)` index | Ensures step execution order without runtime `ORDER BY` |
| Subscription covering indexes | 4 purpose-built indexes on `subscriptions` for all lifecycle query patterns |
| `steps_count` denormalisation | Workflow list performance without `COUNT(*)` joins on every page load |
| Brand AI context in JSON | `tone`, `vocabulary`, `guidelines` stored per-brand for prompt injection |
| `credits_cost` on contents | Per-generation cost tracked at the content level for usage auditing |
| Affiliate multi-level design | `level` tinyint on referrals allows multi-level expansion without schema change |

### Risks and Improvement Opportunities

| Issue | Severity | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|
| Payment credentials in app_settings | High | Move all API keys to environment variables — DB storage is a security risk |
| Single-row `app_settings` table | Medium | No `key` column — any schema change requires a migration; consider key-value pattern |
| `clicks` and `conversions` as counters | Medium | Race condition risk on concurrent updates — use atomic `UPDATE ... SET clicks = clicks + 1` |
| No `user_id` on `content_assets` | Medium | Assets are brand-scoped only — no user-level asset attribution |
| No token usage tracking | Medium | Unlike LabProject, there is no `ai_usage_logs` equivalent — no per-user cost attribution |
| `social_accounts.credentials` in JSON | Medium | OAuth tokens should be encrypted at rest, not plain JSON |
| `weekly_strategies.suggestions` as JSON | Low | AI suggestions not typed — recommend versioned JSON schema for downstream parsing |
| Missing `deleted_at` on `content_versions` | Low | Versions cannot be soft-deleted; hard deletes orphan the audit trail |

