## 13. Data Quality Findings

| Finding | Severity | Detail |
|---|---|---|
| Payment API keys in `app_settings` | High | NowPayments, Stripe, and Paystack keys stored in DB row — must use env vars |
| `clicks`/`conversions` counter race condition | Medium | Concurrent requests can corrupt counters — use atomic SQL updates |
| No token/cost usage tracking | Medium | No `ai_usage_logs` equivalent — impossible to do per-user AI cost attribution |
| `social_accounts.credentials` in plain JSON | Medium | OAuth tokens need encryption at rest before production deployment |
| `app_settings` single-row pattern | Medium | Schema changes require migrations; a key-value pattern would be more flexible |
| `affiliate_links` counters not event-sourced | Low | Counter drift possible without event-level click tracking backing them |
| No `user_id` on `content_assets` | Low | Asset ownership is brand-level only — no individual user attribution |
| Test users in production seed | Low | Users 1–4 are `test@example.com`, `testuser@example.com` — should be removed before production |

